text: Hurray! A new Sunrise Express episode! These are my favorite videos on your channel. I want to give you a feedback from my country: Compared to the prizes in Germany, the JR Sunrise express ticket is quite economical, especially considering the travel distance and the fact it is a night train with single sleeping compartment. For this price, you can buy a 1st class ICE ticket (InterCity Express train) from Munich to Hamburg, which is about 765km and 9 to 10 hours of traveling time. You can buy food on board, but it is quite expensive. For the money you spent on food you will get a coffee in the ICE Bistro. It is better to bring own food like you did. So, now I want to see the new episode of Travel Alone on the Sunrise Express! Haha! Best regards from Germany
